THOUGHT: The miscompile occurs because InstCombine folds equality of two GEPs into equality of their offsets unconditionally for equality predicates, even when GEPs may wrap (no inbounds/nowrap). This is controlled by the local CanFold lambda in InstCombineCompares.cpp, which currently returns true for equality regardless of nowrap flags. A safe fix is to require some nowrap property even for equality, i.e., change CanFold to return NW != none() for equality. This will prevent folding when GEPs may wrap (like with p:8:8:8), fixing the Alive2 failure while preserving optimizations when inbounds/nowrap are present.

```bash
python3 - <<'PY'
import re, sys, pathlib
p = pathlib.Path("llvm/lib/Transforms/InstCombine/InstCombineCompares.cpp")
s = p.read_text()
# Modify the CanFold lambda to not unconditionally fold equality. Require nowrap flags.
old = r"""auto CanFold = [Cond](GEPNoWrapFlags NW) {
    if (ICmpInst::isEquality(Cond))
      return true;

    // Unsigned predicates can be folded if the GEPs have *any* nowrap flags.
    assert(ICmpInst::isUnsigned(Cond));
    return NW != GEPNoWrapFlags::none();
  };"""
new = r"""auto CanFold = [Cond](GEPNoWrapFlags NW) {
    if (ICmpInst::isEquality(Cond))
      // Avoid miscompilation on targets with small pointer sizes or maywrap GEPs:
      // Only fold equality if we have some no-wrap proof (e.g. inbounds/NUW/NSW).
      return NW != GEPNoWrapFlags::none();

    // Unsigned predicates can be folded if the GEPs have *any* nowrap flags.
    assert(ICmpInst::isUnsigned(Cond));
    return NW != GEPNoWrapFlags::none();
  };"""
if old not in s:
    # Fallback: more permissive replace of just the equality branch
    s = re.sub(r'(auto\s+CanFold\s*=\s*\[Cond\]\(GEPNoWrapFlags\s+NW\)\s*\{\s*if\s*\(ICmpInst::isEquality\(Cond\)\)\s*)return\s+true;',
               r'\1return NW != GEPNoWrapFlags::none();', s)
else:
    s = s.replace(old, new)
p.write_text(s)
print("Patched CanFold to require nowrap even for equality.")
PY
